snippet.textDisplay: I get where you Whites are coming from, especially from the USA.  However as a former amateur boxer there are some glaring points I think you should consider.  First compare Deontay knocking down Tyson in the first fight, at no time did Tyson "drop" Deontay it was more like being pushed down off balance!  Also with the "stoppage" of the fight, remember Deontay was not stopped by the ref for not being able to fight back or protect himself, neither was he counted out!  Deontay's corner stopped the fight because he was gassed.  Deontay was never "broken of his will to fight"! Tyson  was bigger, had more reach, and out weighted Deontay by 40 lbs, and he used it to his advantage.  Tyson out boxed Deontay both fights as OTHERS have for different times for a period, BUT Deontay young career rocketed to the crown on the phenomenal arm that he was blessed with.  His arm is what makes him so incredible  because at any point he could win gatherless of how far behind he is on the cards.  I respect both men for reaching that level.
